# Calculate distance traveled
from math import radians, cos, sin, sqrt, asin, atan2

def dist(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
    lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2 = map(radians, [lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2])
    dlon = lon2 - lon1
    dlat = lat2 - lat1

    a = (sin(dlat/2))**2 + cos(lat1) * cos(lat2) * (sin(dlon/2))**2
    c = 2 * atan2(sqrt(a), sqrt(1-a))
    dist = 6371 * c  # in kilometers

    return dist

df['dist'] = df.apply(lambda row: dist(row['start_lat'], row['start_lng'], row['end_lat'], row['end_lng']), axis=1)
df['dist'] = np.round(df['dist'], 2)

# Visualize Day and Hours
from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle

grouped_df = df.groupby(['startDay', 'startHour']).agg({'startDay': 'count'})
grouped_df.reset_index(level = 1, inplace = True)
grouped_df['day'] = grouped_df.index
grouped_df.reset_index(drop = True, inplace = True)
grouped_df.columns = ['hour', 'count', 'day']
grouped_df.head()

grouped_df = grouped_df.pivot(index = 'hour', columns = 'day', values = 'count', )
plt.figure(figsize = (5, 6))
ax = sns.heatmap(grouped_df, annot = False, cmap = 'Greens')
plt.title('Ride Stats -  (Hour and Day)', weight = 'bold')
plt.xlabel('Day of the week', weight = 'bold')
plt.ylabel('Hour of the day', weight = 'bold')

# Evening blip
rect = Rectangle((0, 15), 5, 5, linewidth=1.2, edgecolor='#f22952',linestyle = '--', facecolor='none')
ax.add_patch(rect)
ax.text(2.5, 15, 'Afternoon bump', color = 'black', size = 9, ha = 'center', bbox=dict(boxstyle="round,pad=0.3", fc="pink", ec="black", lw=0.5))

# Morning bump
rect = Rectangle((0, 7), 5, 3, linewidth=1.2, edgecolor='#f22952', linestyle = '--', facecolor='none')
ax.add_patch(rect)
ax.text(2.5, 7, 'Morning bump', color = 'black', size = 9, ha = 'center', bbox=dict(boxstyle="round,pad=0.3", fc="pink", ec="black", lw=0.5))

# plt.xticks(ticks = ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'])
ax.set_xticklabels(['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'], rotation = 0, fontdict={'size': 9})
plt.yticks(rotation = 0)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('seaborn_3.png')
plt.show()

# Visualizing importance of stations
# pd.concat([df.groupby(['start_station_name']).agg({'ride_id': 'count'})[0:50],
#           df.groupby(['start_station_name']).agg({'ride_id': 'count'})[df.shape[0] - 50 :df.shape[0]]]).sort_values(by = 'ride_id', ascending=False)
from IPython.display import Image
imp_df = df.groupby(['start_station_name']).agg({'ride_id': 'count'})
imp_df['station'] = imp_df.index
imp_df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
imp_df.columns = ['ridership', 'station']

loc_data = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['start_station_id'], keep = 'first').loc[:, ['start_station_name','start_lat', 'start_lng']]
loc_data = pd.merge(loc_data, imp_df, 
         left_on='start_station_name',
         right_on='station', 
         how='left')
loc_data.sort_values(by=['ridership'], inplace=True, ascending=False)
loc_data.drop(columns = ['start_station_name'], inplace = True)
loc_data.reset_index(drop = True, inplace = True)
loc_data.head(10)

fig = px.scatter_mapbox(loc_data,
                        lat='start_lat',
                        lon='start_lng',
                        color = 'ridership',
                        opacity=0.7,
                        size='ridership',
                        zoom=12,
                        width=800,
                        height=800,
                        mapbox_style='open-street-map',
                        color_continuous_scale='Mint')
fig.update_layout(mapbox_style='carto-positron', title='Blue Bikes Station Importance', title_x = 0.5, showlegend = True)
fig.update_layout(coloraxis_showscale=True,

                 title="Ridership"))
